1
00:01:58,087 --> 00:02:00,885
We are in November 1949.

2
00:02:00,967 --> 00:02:03,800
The location is in the southwest of China ...

3
00:02:03,847 --> 00:02:06,566
where the Red Army has 
not taken control ... yet.

4
00:02:47,607 --> 00:02:50,280
Good morning. 
I'm Father O'Banion.

5
00:02:50,327 --> 00:02:52,557
Good morning, Father. 
I'm Father Lemay.

6
00:02:52,607 --> 00:02:56,441
He should have arrived a long time ago. We 
were told he would get here in a few days.

7
00:02:56,527 --> 00:02:58,643
Well, I designed it, but ...

8
00:02:58,727 --> 00:03:01,799
I had a very difficult trip.

9
00:03:01,887 --> 00:03:06,039
To put it mildly, Father Bovard is already 
looking forward to replacing him.

10
00:03:06,127 --> 00:03:09,403
He still has a 2-day trip to 
San-Li-Wan.

11
00:03:09,447 --> 00:03:12,439
I will tell Father Bovard 
how sorry I am for the delay.

12
00:03:12,527 --> 00:03:14,916
We assumed you were traveling alone.

13
00:03:19,007 --> 00:03:22,556
I guess I should tell 
you why this girl is traveling with me.

14
00:03:24,327 --> 00:03:26,887
We are very curious, yes.

15
00:03:28,487 --> 00:03:31,479
Well ... her mother has just returned ...

16
00:03:31,527 --> 00:03:34,485
and very enthusiastic ...

17
00:03:36,607 --> 00:03:37,801
to embrace faith ...

18
00:03:37,887 --> 00:03:40,447
to learn more about Christianity.

19
00:03:41,567 --> 00:03:43,842
You know, I 
made that unfortunate mistake ...

20
00:03:43,927 --> 00:03:49,126
that I saved this girl from 
the spring flood and ...

21
00:03:49,207 --> 00:03:52,563
There really is a Chinese custom that 
says that if you save a life ...

22
00:03:52,647 --> 00:03:55,002
are you responsible for that life then?

23
00:03:55,087 --> 00:03:56,918
That's a tradition.

24
00:03:57,807 --> 00:03:59,638
But ... doesn't it exaggerate a bit?

25
00:03:59,727 --> 00:04:01,622
Believe me, I 
did my best,

26
00:04:01,622 --> 00:04:03,342
to persuade him not to follow any further.

27
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:07,246
<font style="vertical-align: inherit;"></font>
I interrupted my trip three times and took it home.

28
00:04:07,327 --> 00:04:10,319
The problem is that it’s faster 
than this stubborn horse.

29
00:04:10,407 --> 00:04:12,238
This is extremely unusual, Father.

30
00:04:12,287 --> 00:04:15,643
More unusual? 
It was a nightmare.

31
00:04:15,767 --> 00:04:19,282
Anyway, for the fourth time, I 
managed to get the horse to gallop ...

32
00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:21,005
and I forged a few miles advantage.

33
00:04:21,047 --> 00:04:23,515
And then when I turned around ...

34
00:04:23,567 --> 00:04:25,637
I turned to see him, 
he was there ...

35
00:04:25,727 --> 00:04:29,197
a small figure in the distance.

36
00:04:29,287 --> 00:04:31,118
And then ... what do you think happened?

37
00:04:31,207 --> 00:04:34,483
- I can't imagine. 
- He passed out.

38
00:04:37,287 --> 00:04:40,643
What could I have done? 
I had to go back to revive him.

39
00:04:43,167 --> 00:04:45,078
The point is, I revived it.

40
00:04:45,207 --> 00:04:49,485
And I thought it 
was my duty to continue on my way ...

41
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:54,402
so I put it on the horse and I’m here 
tired and with sore feet.

42
00:04:58,127 --> 00:05:00,277
He recovered quickly.

43
00:05:00,367 --> 00:05:03,200
And now you're sitting in the saddle again 
and running next to you?

44
00:05:03,247 --> 00:05:05,363
Oh father, it's so beautiful here.

45
00:05:05,447 --> 00:05:07,358
Why don't we stay here?

46
00:05:09,287 --> 00:05:12,165
This is a very good idea. 
Please get off.

47
00:05:15,167 --> 00:05:17,476
I will leave you here 
and continue my journey.

48
00:05:17,527 --> 00:05:20,883
And when I’m at a safe distance, 
far from here, they can send me home.

49
00:05:20,967 --> 00:05:23,686
At least that decision makes sense.

50
00:05:23,727 --> 00:05:25,604
I say goodbye.

51
00:05:25,647 --> 00:05:27,842
- Father, you can't leave me here alone. 
- I'm forced.

52
00:05:29,647 --> 00:05:32,923
- I'm going to die. 
- Siu-Lan, you have everything for life.

53
00:05:32,967 --> 00:05:36,323
If you leave without me, there will be no reason to live.

54
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:38,517
I'm going to kill myself.

55
00:05:38,567 --> 00:05:40,478
You have to promise not to.

56
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:43,639
- I promise I'll. 
"It's much worse than he said."

57
00:05:45,327 --> 00:05:48,399
Siu-Lan, committing suicide is a 
bad thing.

58
00:05:48,487 --> 00:05:53,038
You know the difference between right and wrong, 
good and bad.

59
00:05:53,127 --> 00:05:58,042
To love yourself is not good. 
Then I'm really really bad.

60
00:05:58,127 --> 00:06:01,278
Why do I feel so good 
when I'm bad?

61
00:06:02,407 --> 00:06:05,365
Siu-Lan, you are very beautiful and 
as soon as you find a nice young man ...

62
00:06:05,447 --> 00:06:08,803
- You're very beautiful, too. 
"For God's sake, would you say goodbye?"

63
00:06:08,887 --> 00:06:10,718
That's exactly what I'm trying to do.

64
00:06:10,807 --> 00:06:14,561
- Bye bye. 
- Father, please don't leave.

65
00:06:14,647 --> 00:06:16,205
Don't leave.

66
00:06:16,247 --> 00:06:18,726
Just pray that something like this 
doesn’t happen to you.

67
00:06:18,727 --> 00:06:20,843
- Leave me out of this. 
- Help me.

68
00:06:20,927 --> 00:06:22,485
Please.

69
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:26,798
Father, please!

70
00:06:26,887 --> 00:06:30,197
Don't leave! 
Don't leave.

71
00:07:50,062 --> 00:07:51,562
I...

72
00:07:52,386 --> 00:07:53,586
I...

73
00:07:56,487 --> 00:08:00,162
- I'm really a priest. 
- I didn't even think he was a nun.

74
00:08:04,007 --> 00:08:06,123
I assume Father O'Banion himself.

75
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:10,362
I see, I made you angry, Father.

76
00:08:10,407 --> 00:08:13,638
Really? 
I'm trying to cover it up.

77
00:08:15,167 --> 00:08:16,998
I'm terribly sorry I'm so late.

78
00:08:17,047 --> 00:08:20,562
I wasn't waiting for your apology. 
I was waiting for you.

79
00:08:22,487 --> 00:08:25,638
It was quite problematic to get here. 
I can explain ...

80
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:29,316
If you will explain how 
long it took to get here ...

81
00:08:29,407 --> 00:08:31,318
then I don't want to hear it.

82
00:08:31,407 --> 00:08:33,477
I just want to go.

83
00:08:34,201 --> 00:08:35,301
Ah-Wang.

84
00:08:37,047 --> 00:08:39,607
Hurry with those suitcases.

85
00:08:42,007 --> 00:08:43,918
He goes it alone.

86
00:08:49,607 --> 00:08:51,518
Thank you, Ah-Wang.

87
00:08:53,847 --> 00:08:55,439
Finally.

88
00:08:59,527 --> 00:09:02,678
- Well, I see you're ready. 
- What a brilliant observation.

89
00:09:02,727 --> 00:09:04,399
Again.

90
00:09:04,487 --> 00:09:08,685
<font style="vertical-align: inherit;"></font>
I've been ready for six seemingly endless days and six sleepless nights ...

91
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:12,077
with a 
weak heart skipping every second beat .

92
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:17,960
In the last six days, I've realized I 
can't waste a minute.

93
00:09:18,007 --> 00:09:19,599
You know ...

94
00:09:19,687 --> 00:09:22,645
I got away after 25 years ...

95
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:24,803
and I better get out of here right away ...

96
00:09:24,847 --> 00:09:27,077
before the red villains 
invade from the north.

97
00:09:28,447 --> 00:09:30,324
They are pushing forward very quickly.

98
00:09:30,407 --> 00:09:34,195
- Did you hear? 
- Yes, this is a rumor.

99
00:09:38,287 --> 00:09:40,960
Do you not enlighten about 
the mission?

100
00:09:43,727 --> 00:09:44,921
Of course.

101
00:09:45,007 --> 00:09:47,123
He is Ah-Wang, his maid and cook.

102
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:51,759
He will show you where he will sleep and eat.

103
00:09:51,847 --> 00:09:53,678
There's the chapel.

104
00:09:57,327 --> 00:09:58,919
Charming.

105
00:09:59,927 --> 00:10:01,519
And there are the nuns.

106
00:10:03,087 --> 00:10:05,157
Do you know some Chinese?

107
00:10:05,287 --> 00:10:07,721
Very little. 
You know, I didn't have time ...

108
00:10:07,847 --> 00:10:09,877
He was so late 
that he could have learned Greek.

109
00:10:09,887 --> 00:10:13,675
Well, luckily, 
some speak English.

110
00:10:13,727 --> 00:10:16,058
They know as much about this mission 
as I do.

111
00:10:19,167 --> 00:10:21,727
Forgive me. 
Damn.

112
00:10:28,567 --> 00:10:30,603
And now, the moment I've been waiting for.

113
00:10:31,727 --> 00:10:34,116
Father O'Banion, goodbye.

114
00:10:34,207 --> 00:10:36,038
Until we meet again, Father.

115
00:10:36,127 --> 00:10:38,846
Please, I want to leave happily.

116
00:11:08,207 --> 00:11:11,005
Father, do you want to meet Sister Teresa?

117
00:11:11,047 --> 00:11:13,845
She's in the nursing home.

118
00:11:17,367 --> 00:11:18,959
Yes, of course.

119
00:11:24,647 --> 00:11:27,036
Sister Teresa, this is Father O'Banion.

120
00:11:27,087 --> 00:11:30,477
"Father Bovard spoke of you, Father." 
- Yes.

121
00:11:30,567 --> 00:11:33,035
I can imagine.

122
00:11:33,127 --> 00:11:36,164
- Well, do we have it here? 
- A badly inflamed throat.

123
00:11:36,207 --> 00:11:39,324
We try to keep 
kids healthy , but someone always gets sick.

124
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:44,284
How do you say "say A" in Chinese?

125
00:11:50,807 --> 00:11:53,196
- Do they have penicillin? 
- Yes, but it's hard to get.

126
00:11:53,287 --> 00:11:55,881
We try to 
reserve for the most serious cases.

127
00:11:55,927 --> 00:11:58,566
Sister, what's more important than a little boy?

128
00:11:58,607 --> 00:12:00,518
All right, father.

129
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:03,206
You'll be better in less than a minute, buddy.

130
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:08,197
Hey, that was a good right.

131
00:12:10,007 --> 00:12:12,760
I made you a delicious rice cake.

132
00:12:14,087 --> 00:12:15,918
You're an excellent cook, Ah-Wang.

133
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:18,322
Father Bovard was lucky 
to find himself.

134
00:12:18,447 --> 00:12:23,282
Yes. 
But sometimes he was very angry with me.

135
00:12:23,327 --> 00:12:27,240
- Why? 
- I stole church wine.

136
00:12:29,447 --> 00:12:31,722
Didn't you keep it locked up?

137
00:12:31,807 --> 00:12:34,002
I also stole the key.

138
00:12:35,127 --> 00:12:37,516
He's good. But other than that ...

139
00:12:37,607 --> 00:12:39,802
you're a good Christian, aren't you?

140
00:12:39,847 --> 00:12:42,042
Oh yes.

141
00:12:42,127 --> 00:12:44,118
So if you shut down the wine ...

142
00:12:44,207 --> 00:12:46,163
i know how to steal.

143
00:12:46,247 --> 00:12:49,956
This is how I will be a good Christian in many ways.

144
00:12:50,007 --> 00:12:53,363
Father Bovard said 
there was something good in everyone ...

145
00:12:53,447 --> 00:12:55,039
even in me.

146
00:13:01,327 --> 00:13:02,362
Communists.

147
00:13:04,647 --> 00:13:07,115
Father Bovard was arrested.

148
00:13:08,327 --> 00:13:09,919
Poor Father Bovard.

149
00:13:17,287 --> 00:13:20,324
I am sorry, Father, 
that your journey has been so short.

150
00:13:20,407 --> 00:13:23,683
Thanks to you, I 
may never leave China.

151
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:26,804
These red devils don’t tell you 
why they brought you back.

152
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:31,118
All they do is smile at me 
and nail their gun to me.

153
00:13:35,647 --> 00:13:38,480
Maybe I'll get an answer from the big boss.

154
00:13:40,447 --> 00:13:43,564
- Ho-San. 
- Colonel in the Red Army.

155
00:13:48,982 --> 00:13:50,982
Ho-San.

156
00:13:51,007 --> 00:13:55,398
Are you one of those people 
and in this uniform?

157
00:13:55,447 --> 00:13:58,678
I wear it with pleasure and pride, 
old man.

158
00:13:58,767 --> 00:14:02,097
You are the last person in the world 
I expected to lead ...

159
00:14:02,147 --> 00:14:04,960
these terrible enemies of the church.

160
00:14:05,047 --> 00:14:07,766
Choose your words, foreign priest.

161
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:09,607
Just so you know, 
I was sent here ...

162
00:14:09,607 --> 00:14:13,998
One moment, new boy. 
Are you still on duty?

163
00:14:14,047 --> 00:14:15,765
Again.

164
00:14:15,807 --> 00:14:18,560
Stay out of this. 
It's up to him and me.

165
00:14:18,647 --> 00:14:22,356
Ho-San, you owe me an explanation.

166
00:14:22,447 --> 00:14:26,122
How can a man with your mind ...

167
00:14:26,207 --> 00:14:29,005
to get involved in this disgraceful situation?

168
00:14:29,127 --> 00:14:32,915
Until you can master your language, 
I suggest we go inside.

169
00:14:32,967 --> 00:14:35,925
Do you suggest? 
I demand.

170
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:14,844
Are you feeling better, Father?

171
00:15:14,927 --> 00:15:18,317
I couldn't sleep, so I came here.

172
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:20,244
I have encouraging news.

173
00:15:20,287 --> 00:15:23,836
A sign was painted on the mission wall.

174
00:15:23,927 --> 00:15:27,397
The sisters were very happy. 
Guarantees freedom of religion ...

175
00:15:27,447 --> 00:15:30,245
and that they will not disturb 
the converts.

176
00:15:30,287 --> 00:15:32,243
How long?

177
00:15:32,327 --> 00:15:35,524
So I do not know. I took a walk out there, 
no one stopped me.

178
00:15:37,487 --> 00:15:39,478
I am very weak...

179
00:15:39,567 --> 00:15:42,035
and probably guilty of self-pity.

180
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:46,684
I wish the Lord had called me 
before I could see Ho-San.

181
00:15:49,247 --> 00:15:52,717
I have a hard time believing 
he was ever a Christian.

182
00:15:55,807 --> 00:15:58,196
Come here. Look.

183
00:15:59,287 --> 00:16:03,200
He’s here after he was a 
minister boy at his first Mass.

184
00:16:03,287 --> 00:16:05,118
He smiles because he made no mistake.

185
00:16:07,287 --> 00:16:12,122
As he grew older, 
we talked for a long time that he might become a priest.

186
00:16:12,207 --> 00:16:16,758
I even saw in front of me 
that one day he would take over the mission.

187
00:16:16,847 --> 00:16:20,283
- Well ... 
- You don't have to say.

188
00:16:20,367 --> 00:16:22,517
He will probably take over.

189
00:16:25,127 --> 00:16:26,719
It's already here ...

190
00:16:31,567 --> 00:16:34,877
I shouldn't think about it.

191
00:16:34,927 --> 00:16:36,804
I'm sorry.

192
00:16:36,887 --> 00:16:39,445
If I remember correctly, my father 
wanted to tell me when he arrived ...

193
00:16:39,447 --> 00:16:42,120
difficulties in arriving here.

194
00:16:42,207 --> 00:16:44,118
But I didn't have time to listen.

195
00:16:44,167 --> 00:16:47,443
Well, I have time now.

196
00:16:48,687 --> 00:16:51,485
Father, it has been a very difficult day.

197
00:16:51,567 --> 00:16:54,206
I wouldn't burden you with my little worries.

198
00:16:55,207 --> 00:16:57,767
- Good night. 
- Father.

199
00:16:57,807 --> 00:17:01,846
If you open that display case, 
you will find a bottle of rice wine.

200
00:17:01,927 --> 00:17:05,966
Maybe we both sleep better 
if we take a sip of it.

201
00:17:06,047 --> 00:17:07,639
Great idea.

202
00:17:16,287 --> 00:17:19,165
Wait. 
What about the morning mass?

203
00:17:19,287 --> 00:17:21,323
We can't eat anything after midnight.

204
00:17:22,487 --> 00:17:26,116
- What time is it? 
- I have 5 minutes in midnight.

205
00:17:26,167 --> 00:17:28,476
With me in a minute.

206
00:17:28,527 --> 00:17:30,677
Are we adjusting to my watch?

207
00:18:04,807 --> 00:18:06,877
Good morning, Father.

208
00:18:06,967 --> 00:18:08,923
We have a beautiful day.

209
00:18:08,967 --> 00:18:11,322
What is so "beautiful beautiful"?

210
00:18:11,367 --> 00:18:13,676
- Did you drink church wine? 
- He is not.

211
00:18:13,727 --> 00:18:15,797
Never during the day.

212
00:18:15,887 --> 00:18:19,436
What are you doing here? He doesn't cook anything 
and the table isn't ready.

213
00:18:19,567 --> 00:18:22,320
I'm ready. 
I'm ready to resign.

214
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:25,200
- What? 
"Would you tell Father Bovard, please?"

215
00:18:25,327 --> 00:18:27,277
"By the time he gets angry, I'm gone." 
-Wait a minute.

216
00:18:27,287 --> 00:18:29,323
Why are you giving up?

217
00:18:29,367 --> 00:18:31,358
Colonel Ho-San spoke to me.

218
00:18:31,407 --> 00:18:33,443
He quickly understood with me 
that I better resign ...

219
00:18:33,527 --> 00:18:36,803
and I will be a happy comrade 
rather than an unhappy dead Christian.

220
00:18:36,887 --> 00:18:38,559
So I...

221
00:18:39,527 --> 00:18:41,563
I stayed too long.

222
00:18:41,647 --> 00:18:45,640
It seems disgusting, but 
I prayed for a rosary for Ho-San ...

223
00:18:45,727 --> 00:18:47,683
I prayed that I would not lose it completely.

224
00:18:47,767 --> 00:18:49,678
You better start praying for Ah-Wang.

225
00:18:49,727 --> 00:18:52,002
He lost him. 
He resigned.

226
00:18:52,087 --> 00:18:55,875
I'm sorry, Father. But Ho-San said 
it makes him very happy.

227
00:18:55,967 --> 00:19:00,199
You little, ungrateful traitor.

228
00:19:00,327 --> 00:19:03,285
Is that the only way you give up your Christian faith?

229
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:06,564
Oh, no, Father. 
I'm just changing my appearance.

230
00:19:06,647 --> 00:19:09,320
Inside, I remain the same Christian.

231
00:19:09,407 --> 00:19:12,444
Bye bye. 
I will pray for you.

232
00:19:12,527 --> 00:19:14,279
What's in the package?

233
00:19:14,367 --> 00:19:16,756
Only personal stuff.

234
00:19:16,847 --> 00:19:19,156
Of course, personal belongings. 
Open up.

235
00:19:19,247 --> 00:19:20,839
Open ...

236
00:19:23,447 --> 00:19:27,281
I'd rather go to the happy gathering of the People's Party.

237
00:19:31,887 --> 00:19:34,765
What kind of convert are I?

238
00:19:34,847 --> 00:19:38,362
I lost Ho-San first, 
and now Ah-Wang.

239
00:19:39,527 --> 00:19:43,805
Inside Christian Ah-Wang. 
Outward thief Ah-Wang.

240
00:19:45,727 --> 00:19:48,560
Well, Father O'Banion, 
let's face it.

241
00:19:48,607 --> 00:19:52,282
I am your pastor and I 
do not intend to be your home servant.

242
00:19:52,367 --> 00:19:55,245
- Can you cook? 
- A little. Nothing special.

243
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:57,158
We don't need specials.

244
00:19:57,247 --> 00:19:59,317
Well, if you want to try ...

245
00:19:59,407 --> 00:20:01,762
I 
shouldn't risk my stomach , but ...

246
00:20:01,807 --> 00:20:03,684
let's see what he can do instead of Ah-Wang.

247
00:20:03,767 --> 00:20:05,860
Just heat 
the canned beef ...

248
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:07,822
and prepare the egg powder.

249
00:20:07,847 --> 00:20:11,237
I ate egg powder when I 
served in the Navy.

250
00:20:11,327 --> 00:20:13,158
Remember how to make it?

251
00:20:13,247 --> 00:20:15,158
I couldn't do worse.

252
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:26,156
- I hope ... 
- Me too.

253
00:20:29,967 --> 00:20:31,559
Not bad.

254
00:20:32,807 --> 00:20:34,763
He warmed it up very well.

255
00:20:40,007 --> 00:20:43,397
- What is this? 
- Scrambled eggs from egg powder.

256
00:20:51,327 --> 00:20:53,238
Not something good, is it, Father?

257
00:20:59,407 --> 00:21:02,285
Father O'Banion, he has 
surpassed the Navy.

258
00:21:02,407 --> 00:21:05,638
Why did you test on me ...? 
If you served this to someone ...

259
00:21:05,727 --> 00:21:08,480
- I do not know what to say. 
- Well, I know.

260
00:21:08,527 --> 00:21:12,122
If you had arrived on time, 
I would n't have wolf-eyed this ...

261
00:21:12,167 --> 00:21:14,362
Name it, grab it and bury it.

262
00:21:14,447 --> 00:21:16,961
- Do mine without it. 
- It took away my appetite.

263
00:21:44,007 --> 00:21:45,281
What happens now?

264
00:22:02,567 --> 00:22:04,558
Colonel Ho-San sent the children home.

265
00:22:04,647 --> 00:22:06,956
And he said he 
couldn’t provide our protection.

266
00:22:07,047 --> 00:22:10,323
I think we should 
be grateful for your efforts.

267
00:22:11,287 --> 00:22:13,482
We learned 
that after complete liberation ...

268
00:22:13,567 --> 00:22:15,797
a 
period of aggression and retaliation ensues.

269
00:22:15,847 --> 00:22:17,644
It's best if the sisters leave.

270
00:22:17,727 --> 00:22:21,800
Now pack up, my car is in the trash 
to take you to the bus.

271
00:22:21,847 --> 00:22:24,566
We only 
accept instructions from Father Bovard .

272
00:22:24,607 --> 00:22:26,757
They can only take us by force.

273
00:22:26,807 --> 00:22:29,367
I admire their courage, sisters ...

274
00:22:29,447 --> 00:22:31,438
but I have to think seriously.

275
00:22:31,527 --> 00:22:34,439
Old man, from now on I will think.

276
00:22:34,527 --> 00:22:37,087
I respect the sisters ...

277
00:22:37,167 --> 00:22:39,144
but 
I may take them away by force.

278
00:22:39,167 --> 00:22:43,319
Ho-San, 
you're still talking like a little boy.

279
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:45,358
They make my job very difficult.

280
00:22:45,407 --> 00:22:49,116
And we will continue to do so.

281
00:22:52,487 --> 00:22:54,318
What about your posters out there?

282
00:22:54,407 --> 00:22:57,763
They guarantee that they 
will not interfere with the work of converts.

283
00:22:57,807 --> 00:23:01,197
New boy, his knowledge of their Chinese is 
very limited.

284
00:23:01,287 --> 00:23:03,926
We guarantee freedom of religion.

285
00:23:04,007 --> 00:23:07,886
Educating Chinese children is 
our responsibility.

286
00:23:08,007 --> 00:23:11,363
For the 
time being, the teachers of the People's Party will take over the work.

287
00:23:13,887 --> 00:23:16,481
Is there anything I can do 
to make you feel even more pleasant?

288
00:23:16,567 --> 00:23:19,286
Yes. 
Burn in hell.

289
00:23:21,327 --> 00:23:23,158
I can't burn in your hell.

290
00:23:23,247 --> 00:23:25,203
I am no longer a believer.

291
00:23:30,487 --> 00:23:33,047
<font style="vertical-align: inherit;"></font>
I find this new freedom limited.

292
00:23:33,127 --> 00:23:36,278
It’s like 
being squeezed with an invisible rope.

293
00:23:36,327 --> 00:23:40,161
I wonder what this "new freedom" 
will bring tomorrow.

294
00:23:40,287 --> 00:23:43,006
Today is not over.

295
00:23:57,047 --> 00:24:00,039
Ho-San seized 
his horse and jeep.

296
00:24:01,167 --> 00:24:03,158
This is the service instruction about it.

297
00:24:06,127 --> 00:24:08,357
I don't think we're going anywhere.

298
00:24:08,447 --> 00:24:10,278
I wanted to go.

299
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:13,439
But now I can even stay.

300
00:26:18,327 --> 00:26:20,795
Are you feeling bad, Father?

301
00:26:20,887 --> 00:26:24,004
It's just 
that my heart is no longer young.

302
00:26:26,047 --> 00:26:29,676
I haven't seen it yet, my child, 
though he speaks English.

303
00:26:29,767 --> 00:26:32,884
I learned English at a school in Guangzhou.

304
00:26:32,967 --> 00:26:34,559
Christian?

305
00:26:34,607 --> 00:26:36,757
Not yet, but I'm still learning.

306
00:26:36,807 --> 00:26:38,525
Good. Good.

307
00:26:38,567 --> 00:26:41,718
- Sit down, child. 
- How nice of you.

308
00:26:42,887 --> 00:26:45,321
What brought the wind so far from Guangzhou?

309
00:26:46,607 --> 00:26:50,646
I followed a young man 
who had conquered my heart.

310
00:26:50,767 --> 00:26:53,725
" 
Are you hoping to marry this man?" - Yes, Father.

311
00:26:53,847 --> 00:26:56,003
I think he will reciprocate his love.

312
00:26:58,687 --> 00:27:02,441
He didn't admit it, 
but I know he loves it.

313
00:27:02,527 --> 00:27:05,963
Then follow through 
and persuade him to admit it.

314
00:27:06,047 --> 00:27:09,437
- I'm going to pray for you. 
- Thank you, Father.

315
00:27:12,487 --> 00:27:16,036
But without money, my journey was over.

316
00:27:18,367 --> 00:27:20,562
Well, I can help you out a little.

317
00:27:20,607 --> 00:27:23,644
Not much, just a little.

318
00:27:23,767 --> 00:27:26,725
Father, I'm not looking for alms.

319
00:27:28,087 --> 00:27:31,079
I'll just find a job somehow.

320
00:27:31,167 --> 00:27:33,317
What a beautiful dish.

321
00:27:36,447 --> 00:27:39,598
Tell me, when was the last time you ate?

322
00:27:39,687 --> 00:27:42,565
It's been a long time.

323
00:27:42,647 --> 00:27:46,435
I love to cook 
when the food is so beautiful.

324
00:27:46,527 --> 00:27:48,802
Can you cook well?

325
00:27:48,887 --> 00:27:52,880
My mom said I’m the only one 
who makes a feast out of nothing.

326
00:27:52,927 --> 00:27:57,796
Well, he seems to have found himself 
a temporary job.

327
00:27:58,767 --> 00:28:00,837
Thank you, Father.

328
00:28:00,967 --> 00:28:03,322
My child, I just have ...

329
00:28:03,407 --> 00:28:07,525
my worst chef 
in all of busy and free China.

330
00:28:07,567 --> 00:28:10,400
- Come with me. 
- Share your burden with me.

331
00:28:10,447 --> 00:28:12,802
It brought light into a very dark day, my 
child.

332
00:28:12,887 --> 00:28:14,718
Mine to you.

333
00:28:14,807 --> 00:28:18,117
I can't wait 
to tell the news to Father O'Banion.

334
00:28:18,207 --> 00:28:19,765
Careful.

335
00:28:31,767 --> 00:28:34,327
What are you boiling now?

336
00:28:34,407 --> 00:28:36,841
- Just water. 
- Thank God.

337
00:28:36,927 --> 00:28:39,839
Well, one of my concerns has been resolved.

338
00:28:39,887 --> 00:28:42,401
He will be replaced as a chef.

339
00:28:42,487 --> 00:28:45,206
I share your relief. 
But who would take the courage ...?

340
00:28:52,567 --> 00:28:53,761
Come in, my child.

341
00:28:55,527 --> 00:28:57,563
Give me, let me help.

342
00:28:59,127 --> 00:29:00,355
Here you go.

343
00:29:01,967 --> 00:29:05,277
Father, this is almost a miracle.

344
00:29:05,367 --> 00:29:08,245
On the edge of the village, I found exactly 
who we needed.

345
00:29:08,327 --> 00:29:10,158
Heaven sent it.

346
00:29:10,247 --> 00:29:12,124
Look.

347
00:29:12,167 --> 00:29:13,726
In addition to being an excellent chef,

348
00:29:13,726 --> 00:29:16,142
you know how to 
grow herbs for my heart.

349
00:29:16,167 --> 00:29:19,000
His name is Siu-Lan.

350
00:29:19,047 --> 00:29:23,882
- Yes. 
"This is Father O'Banion, my child."

351
00:29:30,887 --> 00:29:34,596
Can I take off my apron? 
It doesn't suit you, Father.

352
00:29:34,647 --> 00:29:36,763
Father, we are back to life today.

353
00:29:36,807 --> 00:29:41,756
Show him where things are. 
I'll be back if I've read enough.

354
00:29:47,287 --> 00:29:49,243
Would you help me, father?

355
00:29:49,327 --> 00:29:50,919
Do it yourself.

356
00:29:52,527 --> 00:29:54,757
I'm so glad to see you.

357
00:29:54,807 --> 00:29:56,798
I'm sorry I 
ca n't say the same.

358
00:29:56,887 --> 00:30:00,800
Her lips don’t, but her eyes say 
she’s glad to see you again.

359
00:30:00,887 --> 00:30:03,276
If you want me to be happy, 
leave immediately.

360
00:30:03,407 --> 00:30:05,284
He doesn't say that seriously.

361
00:30:05,407 --> 00:30:08,797
Isn’t it bad for a priest to say something 
he doesn’t mean seriously?

362
00:30:11,287 --> 00:30:13,403
It's alright then.

363
00:30:13,487 --> 00:30:17,321
Stop my harassment. 
You can't stay here.

364
00:30:17,407 --> 00:30:20,126
I'm serious. 
You have to go.

365
00:30:24,727 --> 00:30:26,638
Father Bovard?

366
00:30:28,807 --> 00:30:33,642
- What is it, Siu-Lan? 
- Dad said I had to go.

367
00:30:33,767 --> 00:30:35,359
To go?

368
00:30:36,127 --> 00:30:38,243
Why?

369
00:30:38,327 --> 00:30:40,887
I’ve never heard of a 
female chef on a mission.

370
00:30:41,007 --> 00:30:42,725
Well, now you've heard of it.

371
00:30:42,807 --> 00:30:46,004
It is no more unusual than we have 
female nuns.

372
00:30:46,047 --> 00:30:49,357
Father O'Banion, 
I'm leading this mission ...

373
00:30:49,407 --> 00:30:51,557
and Siu-Lan stays here.

374
00:30:51,607 --> 00:30:55,202
So I would thank you for not interfering 
and getting out of the kitchen.

375
00:30:55,287 --> 00:30:56,879
Yes, father.

376
00:31:05,287 --> 00:31:08,438
Go on, my child. 
The whole kitchen is yours.

377
00:31:08,487 --> 00:31:10,079
Thank you, Father.

378
00:31:13,367 --> 00:31:15,961
Father O'Banion, are you out of your mind?

379
00:31:16,007 --> 00:31:18,999
- It looks awful. 
- Well, I don't feel very well.

380
00:31:19,087 --> 00:31:21,043
It's from your brew.

381
00:31:21,087 --> 00:31:23,237
Whatever it is, I feel bad.

382
00:31:45,807 --> 00:31:48,401
What bad news did you bring now?

383
00:31:48,447 --> 00:31:51,644
I came to invite the 
old priest to hear my speech.

384
00:31:51,727 --> 00:31:55,163
I will speak to the villagers. 
You will surely find it enlightening.

385
00:31:55,247 --> 00:31:57,807
All right. 
"Know your enemy."

386
00:31:58,767 --> 00:32:00,837
- I go. 
- Good.

387
00:32:00,927 --> 00:32:05,762
And another thing. I noticed they 
have a new person in their household.

388
00:32:05,887 --> 00:32:07,286
A beautiful Chinese girl.

389
00:32:07,367 --> 00:32:10,086
Since you took Ah-Wang, 
he will help you in the kitchen.

390
00:32:10,127 --> 00:32:12,038
You don't understand me, old priest.

391
00:32:12,167 --> 00:32:16,206
Chinese. 
That is why he is my responsibility.

392
00:32:16,287 --> 00:32:19,165
With your permission, I'd talk to him.

393
00:32:21,007 --> 00:32:22,963
Only if allowed.

394
00:32:25,567 --> 00:32:29,162
We didn’t even eat a regular meal 
before the devil put his foot down.

395
00:32:29,207 --> 00:32:31,641
He'll send him out of here and see you.

396
00:32:32,687 --> 00:32:34,723
Well, maybe that's how it will be, Father.

397
00:32:34,767 --> 00:32:36,723
You said the best?

398
00:32:36,807 --> 00:32:39,321
- It was just a thought. 
- A silly thought.

399
00:32:39,407 --> 00:32:43,241
It would be better if you prayed to 
leave that girl here safe with us.

400
00:32:46,327 --> 00:32:49,956
I assure you that I will pray a lot.

401
00:33:18,807 --> 00:33:21,640
- Do you think he's abusing him? 
- He was the one who yelled.

402
00:33:21,687 --> 00:33:23,962
Let's go and see.

403
00:33:24,047 --> 00:33:27,119
- What happened? 
- An accident. Nothing.

404
00:33:28,607 --> 00:33:31,679
I interviewed the girl. 
You can stay for now.

405
00:33:32,182 --> 00:33:34,182
Ho-San ...

406
00:33:34,207 --> 00:33:37,438
Is it possible that 
traces of Christianity have remained in you?

407
00:33:37,487 --> 00:33:39,364
Don't insult me, old man.

408
00:33:39,447 --> 00:33:42,007
I can change my mind.

409
00:33:42,087 --> 00:33:44,920
You heard him, Father. 
At least Siu-Lan can stay.

410
00:33:44,967 --> 00:33:46,136
Yes, I heard him.

411
00:33:46,167 --> 00:33:49,045
Siu-Lan, everything is taken care of. 
It can stay.

412
00:33:49,127 --> 00:33:51,800
Thank you, Father. 
I'm very happy.

413
00:33:51,887 --> 00:33:54,879
I did not understand. 
What did Ho-San say?

414
00:33:54,967 --> 00:33:56,798
He said many things.

415
00:33:56,887 --> 00:33:58,718
And he tried to court me.

416
00:33:58,767 --> 00:34:02,123
That's not interesting. 
What he said?

417
00:34:02,207 --> 00:34:05,119
He said I had to report everything the 
two of you do.

418
00:34:05,167 --> 00:34:07,681
- Everything? 
- Do not worry.

419
00:34:07,727 --> 00:34:10,639
- I'll tell him good. 
- God bless you, child.

420
00:34:10,727 --> 00:34:14,845
So now 
I’m a cook, a washer and a spy.

421
00:34:14,927 --> 00:34:17,157
I feel the loop is getting tighter.

422
00:34:18,167 --> 00:34:20,044
How right you are.

423
00:35:13,407 --> 00:35:14,999
God bless you.

424
00:35:30,687 --> 00:35:34,885
There were crowds in Ho-San’s speech, I 
wondered if anyone was here.

425
00:35:34,927 --> 00:35:36,519
I'll see.

426
00:35:58,767 --> 00:36:01,565
Our congregation is only from Ho-San's 
father and mother ...

427
00:36:01,647 --> 00:36:03,319
and of course the sisters.

428
00:36:03,407 --> 00:36:06,479
God bless them. 
And from two loyal minister boys.

429
00:36:06,567 --> 00:36:08,478
Let's start the Mass.

430
00:37:45,087 --> 00:37:47,396
Are you worried about something, Father?

431
00:37:47,487 --> 00:37:49,398
I'm thinking about the future.

432
00:37:50,927 --> 00:37:55,284
Do you mean Christians 
who are already afraid to come to church?

433
00:37:55,367 --> 00:37:57,642
Again.

434
00:37:57,727 --> 00:38:00,685
And if they never come back?

435
00:38:00,767 --> 00:38:04,840
What will happen then? 
Where are we going?

436
00:38:04,887 --> 00:38:06,764
Where are we going ?!

437
00:38:06,847 --> 00:38:09,156
I will go where the bishop sends me.

438
00:38:09,247 --> 00:38:12,159
And your instruction does not apply to you.

439
00:38:12,207 --> 00:38:14,163
I wish I could talk to your bishop.

440
00:38:14,207 --> 00:38:17,404
- I could understand him. 
- What would you understand with him?

441
00:38:17,487 --> 00:38:20,763
- U.S. 
- U.S?

442
00:38:21,607 --> 00:38:25,919
Anything you could say about us could 
only be an imaginary fairy tale.

443
00:38:26,007 --> 00:38:28,999
Not imaginary, beautiful.

444
00:38:29,127 --> 00:38:32,563
You are the blonde prince 
and I am the chosen one of your heart.

445
00:38:32,687 --> 00:38:34,882
It is written that much torment ...

446
00:38:34,927 --> 00:38:37,521
and we will go through a storm together.

447
00:38:37,607 --> 00:38:40,724
But once the Sun emerges from the clouds ...

448
00:38:40,807 --> 00:38:43,196
and love will 
prevail over all.

449
00:38:43,287 --> 00:38:46,120
- You're crazy. 
- Are you crazy?

450
00:38:46,207 --> 00:38:48,757
- You mean, like, really crazy? 
- Yes, he's really crazy.

451
00:38:49,607 --> 00:38:51,199
Explain.

452
00:38:51,287 --> 00:38:55,200
I mean, fool. 
He knows a priest can't get married.

453
00:38:55,287 --> 00:38:56,959
I made a vow. 
I swore.

454
00:38:57,047 --> 00:39:00,517
- You mean in life? 
- That's right.

455
00:39:00,607 --> 00:39:03,565
Then you're crazy. 
Other foreign priests may marry.

456
00:39:03,687 --> 00:39:07,396
I knew a priest 
who had two wives and six children.

457
00:39:07,487 --> 00:39:10,445
So if your first wife dies, you can 
take another one.

458
00:39:10,527 --> 00:39:14,042
He is not a priest. 
He's a Protestant ... a pastor.

459
00:39:14,087 --> 00:39:16,681
They have to get married.

460
00:39:17,647 --> 00:39:19,717
We also have a happy ending.

461
00:39:19,807 --> 00:39:21,638
He becomes a Protestant.

462
00:39:22,647 --> 00:39:25,036
That I...?

463
00:39:26,087 --> 00:39:28,237
You're ridiculous. 
I've been staying too long already.

464
00:39:28,287 --> 00:39:30,437
But ... father?

465
00:39:30,487 --> 00:39:33,445
Father O'Banion? 
Father O'Banion!

466
00:39:33,527 --> 00:39:37,918
Father! I'm sorry I hurt you. 
Please don't be angry.

467
00:39:41,207 --> 00:39:42,435
Father O'Banion?

468
00:39:42,527 --> 00:39:44,961
When you’re not too busy, 
I want to talk to you.

469
00:39:45,047 --> 00:39:46,958
Yes, father.

470
00:39:53,207 --> 00:39:55,243
Tones inside.

471
00:40:21,727 --> 00:40:23,797
Don't play hide and seek with me.

472
00:40:24,767 --> 00:40:26,723
Come here now.

473
00:40:28,007 --> 00:40:30,077
Father, you better calm down.

474
00:40:30,127 --> 00:40:32,516
- Because of his heart, you know. 
- Shall I calm down?

475
00:40:32,607 --> 00:40:35,246
With 
yourself who is probably hugging in the back ...

476
00:40:35,327 --> 00:40:37,363
with our beautiful young chef?

477
00:40:37,447 --> 00:40:39,517
He seemed to be stroking it.

478
00:40:39,647 --> 00:40:41,638
I didn’t hug or caress her.

479
00:40:41,767 --> 00:40:43,758
I was just trying to push it aside.

480
00:40:43,847 --> 00:40:47,920
Then he put his hand 
on me and I freed myself.

481
00:40:47,967 --> 00:40:51,676
- I interrupted. 
"What did you interrupt, Father?"

482
00:40:51,767 --> 00:40:54,998
Anything you two ... 
That's exactly what I 'm trying to find out.

483
00:40:55,087 --> 00:40:57,920
Why did you have to push him aside?

484
00:40:59,087 --> 00:41:00,918
Because of what happened in the garden.

485
00:41:01,007 --> 00:41:03,475
I was afraid of that. 
Well.

486
00:41:03,567 --> 00:41:05,159
Kivele.

487
00:41:08,967 --> 00:41:10,446
Do you think this is the subject of a joke?

488
00:41:12,167 --> 00:41:15,443
I'm sorry, Father, but it's so tragic 
it's funny.

489
00:41:15,487 --> 00:41:17,398
I'll decide.

490
00:41:17,447 --> 00:41:20,086
Tell me in a laughable, 
careless way.

491
00:41:21,127 --> 00:41:23,038
What happened in the garden?

492
00:41:26,327 --> 00:41:29,478
He asked me ... to marry me.

493
00:41:32,767 --> 00:41:37,283
He asked that ... 
And you agreed, of course.

494
00:41:38,247 --> 00:41:40,602
And now he has come to ask for my blessing.

495
00:41:41,927 --> 00:41:43,519
When will the wedding be?

496
00:41:45,207 --> 00:41:48,165
- Father, it's not time to fool around. 
- How right you are.

497
00:41:48,287 --> 00:41:50,965
He noticed that he had suddenly 
replaced the Communists,

498
00:41:50,965 --> 00:41:52,762
as my biggest problem?

499
00:41:53,487 --> 00:41:55,557
I did not encourage the girl.

