01:01:36,327 --> 01:01:40,081
- You shouldn't ... 
- Father O'Banion, are you awake?

742
01:01:42,167 --> 01:01:43,361
Again.

743
01:01:49,687 --> 01:01:53,805
- What went out the window? 
- We? What?

744
01:01:53,847 --> 01:01:56,236
That's exactly what I'm asking you.

745
01:01:56,327 --> 01:01:58,238
What went out the window?

746
01:02:00,047 --> 01:02:03,926
- It could have been a bat. 
- A bat? In slippers?

747
01:02:06,207 --> 01:02:09,597
Father, you know without your glasses 
your vision is a bit blurry.

748
01:02:09,687 --> 01:02:12,884
It's not so vague. 
Why did you hesitate?

749
01:02:12,927 --> 01:02:15,316
Couldn't decide if he was awake?

750
01:02:16,727 --> 01:02:18,285
I was awake.

751
01:02:21,047 --> 01:02:23,356
Forgive me, Father.

752
01:02:23,447 --> 01:02:26,723
I didn’t come to help, but I heard you. 
I'm a spy, as you know.

753
01:02:26,767 --> 01:02:29,804
You must not 
think badly of Father O'Banion.

754
01:02:29,847 --> 01:02:32,407
- I'm trying not to think. 
- I heard the bell.

755
01:02:32,487 --> 01:02:35,479
And I came to ask what 
he wanted, and he said that ...

756
01:02:35,527 --> 01:02:40,123
the bell fell off the table as 
he turned off the lamp.

757
01:02:40,167 --> 01:02:43,079
I see it from here. I'll pick it up.

758
01:02:45,767 --> 01:02:48,725
- Do you see? 
- Yes, it's clear.

759
01:02:48,807 --> 01:02:53,039
- It's clear. "Go to your room immediately, you 
little bat."

760
01:02:53,087 --> 01:02:54,679
Yes, father.

761
01:02:57,047 --> 01:02:59,322
And 
use the door for variety .

762
01:03:00,687 --> 01:03:02,279
Yes, father.

763
01:03:07,807 --> 01:03:09,843
How could Father O'Banion?

764
01:03:09,927 --> 01:03:13,283
In my long life, 
I didn’t know a person like you.

765
01:03:13,367 --> 01:03:16,165
It added a new dimension to the priestly vocation.

766
01:03:38,687 --> 01:03:40,598
Sisters, did you see ...?

767
01:03:41,687 --> 01:03:44,281
- Father Bovard, you should rest. 
- That's what we said.

768
01:03:44,367 --> 01:03:47,007
- But he's not listening to us. 
- We can do the garden work too.

769
01:03:47,007 --> 01:03:50,158
So should I rest? 
In addition to a million and a problem?

770
01:03:51,767 --> 01:03:55,680
And speaking of problems, sisters, 
if they did, they would leave us alone ...

771
01:03:55,767 --> 01:03:57,997
i think i can solve one now.

772
01:03:58,087 --> 01:04:00,396
As you wish, Father.

773
01:04:06,727 --> 01:04:11,357
Father O'Banion, before further embarrassing 
his own name and his church ...

774
01:04:11,447 --> 01:04:13,039
Siu-Lan has to go.

775
01:04:14,647 --> 01:04:17,957
I agree with you. 
We have to send it.

776
01:04:18,047 --> 01:04:22,802
I wish I could be absolutely convinced 
that the desire he felt for me was bad.

777
01:04:22,887 --> 01:04:26,675
- I thought I might have made some 
progress, but ... - Progress?

778
01:04:26,767 --> 01:04:29,156
The last time he was in his room.

779
01:04:29,247 --> 01:04:32,762
If I hadn't intervened, 
where would they have gone from there?

780
01:04:32,847 --> 01:04:37,443
Father O'Banion, I have 
a question.

781
01:04:37,527 --> 01:04:41,566
When Siu-Lan came here, he said 
he was looking for the man he was in love with.

782
01:04:43,367 --> 01:04:45,483
Did you find him?

783
01:04:46,767 --> 01:04:48,359
Again.

784
01:04:50,007 --> 01:04:51,918
Jesus, Mary and Joseph.

785
01:04:51,967 --> 01:04:54,925
So I prayed 
that he would come with you.

786
01:04:54,967 --> 01:04:59,199
You have to go now. It's in the garden. 
Go and tell me right away.

787
01:04:59,247 --> 01:05:00,839
Yes, father.

788
01:05:15,647 --> 01:05:17,160
- Good morning. 
- Good morning.

789
01:05:17,247 --> 01:05:21,206
I picked up a few flowers on the table to 
decorate for the reheated dinner.

790
01:05:21,287 --> 01:05:24,563
It 
will look like a fresh breakfast with beautiful flowers .

791
01:05:24,647 --> 01:05:26,239
Please, sit down.

792
01:05:30,942 --> 01:05:32,242
Sri Lanka ...

793
01:05:33,067 --> 01:05:35,803
I thought very seriously.

794
01:05:35,847 --> 01:05:38,236
- About us? 
- Yes.

795
01:05:38,287 --> 01:05:40,755
And?

796
01:05:40,807 --> 01:05:43,082
You must leave the mission.

797
01:05:45,687 --> 01:05:47,962
You mean, it's time to say goodbye?

798
01:05:49,247 --> 01:05:50,839
Forever?

799
01:05:52,487 --> 01:05:56,685
But you can’t say it seriously, 
knowing that I love you with all my heart.

800
01:05:56,727 --> 01:06:00,197
If you consider me so important, 
never say that again.

801
01:06:00,327 --> 01:06:03,460
- But you ... - Promise me you'll never 
tell me that again.

802
01:06:10,727 --> 01:06:12,285
All right, father.

803
01:06:15,087 --> 01:06:16,679
I promise...

804
01:06:18,647 --> 01:06:20,558
i will never say ...

805
01:06:21,687 --> 01:06:24,565
that "I love you" again.

806
01:06:26,487 --> 01:06:29,638
But it will always go through my thoughts ...

807
01:06:29,687 --> 01:06:32,201
and in my dreams.

808
01:06:32,327 --> 01:06:35,444
You can't protect yourself from my dreams.

809
01:06:35,527 --> 01:06:37,802
From those beautiful dreams.

810
01:06:37,887 --> 01:06:39,923
That proves you have to go.

811
01:06:43,207 --> 01:06:46,802
I know it's hard to say goodbye.

812
01:06:46,847 --> 01:06:50,522
- Cruel. 
- Maybe, but that's the only solution.

813
01:06:52,807 --> 01:06:54,877
But I will always remember ...

814
01:06:56,407 --> 01:06:58,318
Goodbye, Siu-Lan.

815
01:07:03,687 --> 01:07:06,042
- Father, I can't leave. 
- You have to.

816
01:07:06,127 --> 01:07:07,402
Make a note of my words.

817
01:07:07,426 --> 01:07:10,026
On the next bus that comes through this, you 
will be on it.

818
01:07:10,727 --> 01:07:12,285
I'm going to get off it.

819
01:07:40,727 --> 01:07:43,878
Father Bovard, I can't say a word. 
All our work is in ruins.

820
01:07:43,967 --> 01:07:47,004
They demolish the chapel and 
take everything out of school.

821
01:07:47,087 --> 01:07:50,397
- Maybe if they protested at Ho-San ... 
- That might help.

822
01:07:50,487 --> 01:07:53,240
No. 
It would just deliver more.

823
01:07:53,327 --> 01:07:56,717
I'm sorry, sisters, 
but they can't prevent this.

824
01:07:58,767 --> 01:08:00,359
The nurse.

825
01:08:14,447 --> 01:08:17,086
Our medicines were believed to 
be consecrated water.

826
01:08:17,127 --> 01:08:20,039
Everything was destroyed, 
including penicillin.

827
01:08:20,087 --> 01:08:23,636
They are now spreading diseases 
along with their propaganda.

828
01:08:25,660 --> 01:08:26,860
Oh, no.

829
01:08:59,087 --> 01:09:01,237
Act fast, Ho-San.

830
01:09:02,567 --> 01:09:05,445
My comrades were enthusiastic and went 
beyond my instructions.

831
01:09:05,527 --> 01:09:07,119
For sure.

832
01:09:10,767 --> 01:09:13,327
I 
ordered some changes in the chapel.

833
01:09:13,407 --> 01:09:15,443
Do you want to watch it?

834
01:09:21,847 --> 01:09:25,601
From now on, it will be a 
meeting place for the leaders of the People's Party .

835
01:09:26,582 --> 01:09:28,582
Ho-San ...

836
01:09:28,607 --> 01:09:31,519
We have prayed many times together in this place.

837
01:09:32,607 --> 01:09:36,043
Why you did this 
with this consecrated chapel ...

838
01:09:36,127 --> 01:09:40,040
maybe God 
will be merciful to your miserable soul.

839
01:09:46,567 --> 01:09:49,718
Knowing his worries, 
his heart was still beating.

840
01:09:56,567 --> 01:09:59,718
"Can I do anything, Father?" 
- Nothing.

841
01:10:03,087 --> 01:10:05,362
Ho-San holds a meeting in the chapel.

842
01:10:05,447 --> 01:10:07,836
I think you better not mind 
until you leave.

843
01:10:07,967 --> 01:10:11,198
- Thank you. It will be. 
- Good night.

844
01:11:31,887 --> 01:11:33,764
He's still breathing.

845
01:11:33,807 --> 01:11:36,042
Thanks to sleeping pills, you 
don't know you're here.

846
01:11:36,047 --> 01:11:39,835
Do you have any plans for us to do it tonight 
or tomorrow?

847
01:11:39,967 --> 01:11:42,720
I no longer trust priests.

848
01:12:26,222 --> 01:12:27,622
Father!

849
01:12:28,246 --> 01:12:29,446
Father!

850
01:12:33,322 --> 01:12:34,522
Ho-San!

851
01:12:34,747 --> 01:12:36,022
Stop!

852
01:12:36,046 --> 01:12:37,046
Ho-San!

853
01:13:04,247 --> 01:13:05,839
Dissolve it.

854
01:14:04,807 --> 01:14:07,844
- Father. 
- He didn't sin.

855
01:14:07,927 --> 01:14:10,077
It was unintentional.

856
01:14:11,127 --> 01:14:13,641
I can no longer 
serve you with innocence.

857
01:14:17,287 --> 01:14:18,879
I was hoping ...

858
01:14:24,287 --> 01:14:26,482
I'm going home now.

859
01:14:26,527 --> 01:14:28,119
Oh, my father!

860
01:14:30,443 --> 01:14:31,743
Father!

861
01:14:39,807 --> 01:14:41,843
I brought you some herbal tea.

862
01:14:43,327 --> 01:14:45,636
It will do good to your heart.

863
01:14:45,727 --> 01:14:47,126
Thanks.

864
01:14:47,167 --> 01:14:51,922
And I wrote down how to make it 
when I’m no longer here.

865
01:14:54,047 --> 01:14:58,165
My child, I don't know 
how well Father O'Banion expressed himself ...

866
01:14:58,207 --> 01:15:00,846
but you have to go.

867
01:15:02,327 --> 01:15:06,081
And remember, 
everything happens for the best.

868
01:15:06,167 --> 01:15:08,476
But, Father, if you could ...

869
01:15:08,527 --> 01:15:09,960
My child ...

870
01:15:11,087 --> 01:15:13,885
i am much older and wiser.

871
01:15:13,967 --> 01:15:15,798
And you are so young.

872
01:15:20,847 --> 01:15:23,281
Father, I have just comforted Siu-Lan.

873
01:15:23,407 --> 01:15:25,563
He seems 
very upset for no reason .

874
01:15:26,807 --> 01:15:30,800
I’m sorry I have to be strict, 
but I have no choice.

875
01:15:31,782 --> 01:15:32,782
Sri Lanka ...

876
01:15:33,107 --> 01:15:36,440
One day, with a smile, he 
will remember it all.

877
01:15:38,727 --> 01:15:40,319
Yes, father.

878
01:15:44,807 --> 01:15:48,800
Then you are a great help. 
Why didn't you help me comfort me?

879
01:15:48,887 --> 01:15:50,718
I thought he had said enough.

880
01:15:50,807 --> 01:15:55,119
It seems to be as 
difficult for him as it is for him.

881
01:15:55,247 --> 01:15:57,078
I know divorce is hard ...

882
01:15:57,167 --> 01:15:59,397
but after what happened, 
Father O'Banion, this ...

883
01:16:12,127 --> 01:16:15,836
- Ho-San is calling us. - Tell me you 
're sick. I'm going alone.

884
01:16:21,007 --> 01:16:23,475
- He wants both of us. 
- Why don't you leave me alone?

885
01:16:29,727 --> 01:16:32,958
My glasses. 
My only glasses.

886
01:16:34,887 --> 01:16:37,447
I won't be able to read now.

887
01:16:40,967 --> 01:16:44,277
I will be happy to read it to you 
whenever you wish, Father.

888
01:16:44,367 --> 01:16:45,959
Thanks.

889
01:16:46,927 --> 01:16:49,395
In the meantime, we better 
find out what Ho-San wants ...

890
01:16:49,527 --> 01:16:52,678
otherwise, it may be that St. Peter 
will read it to both of us.

891
01:16:52,727 --> 01:16:54,319
Again.

892
01:17:14,422 --> 01:17:16,422
Uh, Ho-San ...

893
01:17:16,447 --> 01:17:18,039
Sick.

894
01:17:19,447 --> 01:17:21,836
Well, at least he suffers in a luxurious environment.

895
01:17:21,927 --> 01:17:23,804
What's wrong?

896
01:17:23,887 --> 01:17:25,764
Something serious, I hope.

897
01:17:26,807 --> 01:17:30,482
A knife was stabbed in me ... in my back.

898
01:17:31,727 --> 01:17:36,437
Who would do that to a 
person as lovable as you?

899
01:17:39,207 --> 01:17:41,243
That's my business.

900
01:17:44,927 --> 01:17:49,557
But I can assure you that the perpetrator 
will receive the punishment he deserves.

901
01:17:52,087 --> 01:17:53,998
That's why I called myself ...

902
01:17:55,127 --> 01:17:56,879
because the wound became infected.

903
01:17:56,967 --> 01:17:58,923
Good. Good.

904
01:17:59,887 --> 01:18:01,684
That's not funny, old man!

905
01:18:01,767 --> 01:18:05,806
I may be old and I’m not funny, 
but now it looks like I’m going to survive you.

906
01:18:05,847 --> 01:18:08,236
Quiet!

907
01:18:08,327 --> 01:18:10,887
Have a fever. 
40 degrees.

908
01:18:10,967 --> 01:18:15,802
Yes, 41 degrees would be enough already.

909
01:18:15,887 --> 01:18:18,401
Your doctor can 
be sure to treat the infection.

910
01:18:18,487 --> 01:18:22,162
You do not currently have the right medicine.

911
01:18:22,847 --> 01:18:24,758
What a coincidence.

912
01:18:24,887 --> 01:18:26,718
You need penicillin ...

913
01:18:26,807 --> 01:18:29,958
and the enlightened comrades 
destroyed our supply.

914
01:18:31,767 --> 01:18:35,237
In what other mission is penicillin?

915
01:18:35,287 --> 01:18:36,879
And why should we tell?

916
01:18:38,247 --> 01:18:40,105
Because that...

917
01:18:41,727 --> 01:18:46,278
their foolish religion does not allow 
a man to die.

918
01:18:46,367 --> 01:18:48,597
Well, at least that's what you remember.

919
01:18:50,087 --> 01:18:51,805
All right.

920
01:18:51,887 --> 01:18:55,926
Penicillin must be found at 
the Lao-Cham converts ...

921
01:18:56,007 --> 01:18:58,840
if your comrades have 
not yet taken on the mission ...

922
01:18:58,927 --> 01:19:01,282
and destroyed the life-saving medicine.

923
01:19:03,007 --> 01:19:06,886
We have not yet released Lao-Cham.

924
01:19:06,927 --> 01:19:08,883
How unfortunate.

925
01:19:10,367 --> 01:19:13,245
Well, we have nothing to do ...

926
01:19:13,287 --> 01:19:16,438
just wait for the end.

927
01:19:16,739 --> 01:19:18,342
Ho-San ...

928
01:19:18,367 --> 01:19:20,487
I can go on a mission to Lao-Cham 
if you give me permission to

929
01:19:20,487 --> 01:19:22,717
to go through 
communist territory.

930
01:19:24,127 --> 01:19:27,836
- And why would you do that? 
"In return for Father Bovard's freedom."

931
01:19:27,927 --> 01:19:30,157
I take it with me and 
come back alone with penicillin.

932
01:19:30,287 --> 01:19:33,836
No. 
Don't bargain with this devil.

933
01:19:36,847 --> 01:19:39,202
- I accept your offer. 
- Well.

934
01:19:41,327 --> 01:19:44,717
But with just one change.

935
01:19:44,767 --> 01:19:48,362
Leave the old man here 
until he gets back.

936
01:19:49,927 --> 01:19:53,397
- Then he will be released. 
- What security do you give him?

937
01:19:54,647 --> 01:19:55,841
I give it my word.

938
01:19:58,527 --> 01:20:01,280
And I give my word for that too ...

939
01:20:01,367 --> 01:20:03,562
if he doesn't come back ...

940
01:20:07,047 --> 01:20:08,844
he will be killed.

941
01:20:10,727 --> 01:20:12,240
Take the necessary action.

942
01:20:12,327 --> 01:20:13,919
I'm leaving immediately.

943
01:20:15,367 --> 01:20:16,800
Father?

944
01:20:17,647 --> 01:20:20,559
Bye bye. 
And don't come back.

945
01:20:22,047 --> 01:20:23,116
Please.

946
01:20:25,847 --> 01:20:28,077
Then at least drive slowly.

947
01:20:42,487 --> 01:20:45,797
I will be ill from these many shocks.

948
01:20:45,887 --> 01:20:47,798
Can I get out of here now?

949
01:20:48,847 --> 01:20:51,077
I think so now.

950
01:20:58,647 --> 01:21:01,957
Will he get medicine to 
make Ho-San heal?

951
01:21:05,127 --> 01:21:08,437
Is this called 
evil to be reciprocated by good?

952
01:21:08,527 --> 01:21:10,597
Something like that.

953
01:21:10,727 --> 01:21:12,604
Then I would never be a good Christian.

954
01:21:14,367 --> 01:21:17,200
I wish I had dug that knife deeper.

955
01:21:17,247 --> 01:21:20,557
Siu-Lan, you should go beyond 
this bitterness.

956
01:21:22,647 --> 01:21:24,956
But I wish he was dead.

957
01:21:35,087 --> 01:21:38,045
That bus goes to your home.

958
01:21:58,447 --> 01:22:01,166
I never thought 
it would end that way.

959
01:22:03,647 --> 01:22:06,844
She will be home 
safely with her parents soon .

960
01:22:08,767 --> 01:22:11,561
That should be enough for the trip.

961
01:22:14,807 --> 01:22:17,605
- If I could just stay. 
- Please.

962
01:22:17,687 --> 01:22:19,279
Enough of this.

963
01:22:23,207 --> 01:22:24,799
Father?

964
01:22:25,967 --> 01:22:29,039
There is a word in another language ...

965
01:22:29,087 --> 01:22:32,045
which sounds sadder than "goodbye"?

966
01:22:36,322 --> 01:22:37,622
No.

967
01:22:39,047 --> 01:22:41,277
But you have to be sad.

968
01:22:42,727 --> 01:22:45,036
Siu-Lan, I wish you well ...

969
01:22:45,087 --> 01:22:47,726
and happiness.

970
01:22:53,207 --> 01:22:55,402
Maybe you don't have a little photo?

971
01:22:55,447 --> 01:22:57,039
No.

972
01:22:59,367 --> 01:23:00,959
Oh, it's okay.

973
01:23:02,287 --> 01:23:04,676
I will always remember your face.

974
01:23:08,327 --> 01:23:11,319
Will you forget my face, Father?

975
01:23:11,367 --> 01:23:13,039
Of course not.

976
01:23:14,927 --> 01:23:19,603
I know I promised 
not to express my feelings.

977
01:23:21,727 --> 01:23:24,446
Would you tell me how you feel?

978
01:23:28,567 --> 01:23:31,400
Say something 
I can remember forever.

979
01:23:33,087 --> 01:23:35,237
Something I can keep forever.

980
01:23:38,807 --> 01:23:41,605
What would you say if you weren't a priest?

981
01:23:47,327 --> 01:23:49,795
I would answer this:

982
01:23:52,767 --> 01:23:55,884
I will never think of myself again ...

983
01:23:57,807 --> 01:24:00,177
as far as I do at the moment.

984
01:24:03,127 --> 01:24:05,766
Can I take comfort in this?

985
01:24:05,807 --> 01:24:08,162
Again.

986
01:24:12,767 --> 01:24:14,678
The bus is here.

987
01:24:19,807 --> 01:24:22,685
Goodbye, my good friend ...

988
01:24:24,487 --> 01:24:26,079
Father O'Banion.

989
01:24:30,127 --> 01:24:32,197
Bye bye.

990
01:24:32,287 --> 01:24:34,005
Goodbye my friend.

991
01:24:48,567 --> 01:24:50,523
I will always remember ...

992
01:25:59,287 --> 01:26:01,926
I've been waiting for you.

993
01:26:01,967 --> 01:26:04,765
Greetings in the cellar.

994
01:26:04,847 --> 01:26:08,876
Father, I'm afraid 
Ho-San won't let go.

995
