1288
01:49:17,926 --> 01:49:21,680
"Here is my answer to those who tortured me.

1289
01:49:26,126 --> 01:49:27,957
Their leaders are ...

1290
01:49:28,046 --> 01:49:31,197
who destroyed 
their religious freedom ...

1291
01:49:31,246 --> 01:49:33,157
and they humbled themselves 
into slavery. "

1292
01:49:41,126 --> 01:49:45,358
"But they cannot destroy 
their faith in God ...

1293
01:49:45,406 --> 01:49:48,921
if they have the willpower 
to let fire burn in their hearts. "

1294
01:50:05,646 --> 01:50:07,955
I never wanted violence.

1295
01:50:09,926 --> 01:50:12,121
Let's pray ...

1296
01:50:12,166 --> 01:50:15,636
that no one may lose his life because of me.

1297
01:50:43,846 --> 01:50:46,314
I called the barracks to 
report this situation.

1298
01:50:46,366 --> 01:50:49,403
- They're sending reinforcements. 
- No reinforcement required.

1299
01:50:49,486 --> 01:50:52,081
30 armed soldiers 
can control the crowd.

1300
01:51:52,126 --> 01:51:55,084
So can you control this ...?

1301
01:51:55,126 --> 01:51:58,038
So can you control 
this situation with 30 soldiers?

1302
01:51:58,126 --> 01:52:01,277
Some inferior villains from the mountains 
joined the crowd.

1303
01:52:01,326 --> 01:52:05,114
- Priests will be punished for this. "So 
what's your next brilliant idea, Comrade?"

1304
01:52:05,166 --> 01:52:08,397
Public hearing for priests, 
followed by execution.

1305
01:52:11,446 --> 01:52:13,880
Wait.

1306
01:52:13,966 --> 01:52:17,561
Before they take me, 
could I have another thought?

1307
01:52:17,606 --> 01:52:18,675
Me?

1308
01:52:18,766 --> 01:52:21,519
I would suggest that 
you deport the priests now ...

1309
01:52:21,606 --> 01:52:25,155
